{"TopicId":201595,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"is this the smallest rover in ksp??","CreatedByName":"icantthink","CreatedById":211082,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-10T19:55:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"icantthink","CreatedById":211082,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-10T19:55:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2453055510\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2453055510\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-10T20:43:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to Spacecraft Exchange.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ben J. Kerman","CreatedById":204948,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-11T00:07:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it might be. The only way you could make it smaller is if you had Tweakscale!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhelperdude","CreatedById":204462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-11T01:28:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223952498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618099624\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204948\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ben J. Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Ben J. Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it might be. The only way you could make it smaller is if you had Tweakscale!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand with other mods too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-11T02:55:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHint: you only really need a single wheel for a \u0027rover\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E(reaction wheels are awesome)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HyperDraco","CreatedById":188993,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-15T20:12:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeats me, I just used a miniature HECS2\u00A0probe core jam-packed with batteries, an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E, a Communotron 16-S and a literal ton of reaction wheels, that\u0027s still rolling across Eeloo somewhere. I had used an Okto probe with a similar layout but it kinda lasted for 10 minutes and then gave up but still good enough\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}